ress-announcements-plugin/113296?ref=mordauk\">WordPress Announcements Plugin</a> on <a href=\"http://codecanyon.net?ref=mordauk\" title=\"Tons of awesome WordPress plugins\">Code Canyon.net</a> has just been updated to include email notifications for announcements.<br /> <span id=\"more-1637\"></span><br /> Now, whenever an <a href=\"http://demo.pippinspages.com/announcements/\">announcement </a>is made, an email can be automatically sent to all registered users with the contents of the announcement, ensuring that everyone gets informed of the important update.</p><div id=\"attachment_1640\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 294px\"><a href=\"http://pippinspages.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/13-screenshot.png\"><img src=\"http://pippinspages.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/13-screenshot-284x273.png\" alt=\"email announcement notification\" title=\"Email announcement notification\" width=\"284\" height=\"273\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1640\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">The email notification</p></div><p>This image is a screenshot of what the email notifications look like.</p><p>Also included in the plugin update, is the ability to have jQuery site notifications for new announcements. These notifications are small, unobtrusive messages that appear at the top of the screen the first time a visitor loads the website. These are only shown once while a visitor is on the site, regardless of how many pages he/she looks at, but will be shown again the next time they come back to the site.</p><p>Check out my demo page for examples of these features.</p><div class=\"button_small\"><h5 class=\"regcase\"><a href=\"http://demo.pippinspages.com/announcements/\" title=\"button\">Demo</a></h5></div><div class=\"button_small\"><h5 class=\"regcase\"><a href=\"http://codecanyon.net/item/premium-wordpress-announcements-plugin/113296?ref=mordauk\" title=\"button\">Download</a></h5></div><h4 class=\'related-posts-header\'>Related Posts</h4><ul class=\"related-post