ghborhood of St. Paul with her two Pomeranians, Schunka Nunpa and Mumu.\r\n\r\n<strong>David K. Wells III</strong>\r\nDavid is a real estate professional specializing in upper bracket residential and commercial real estate sales. He is passionate about responsible urban redevelopment and affordable housing issues, focusing on exciting and innovative strategies to continually create great neighborhoods. As a straight son of his gay father, David has grown up to become a fervent advocate of GLBT rights and social justice issues. David’s past work includes serving on the board of directors of the Twin Cities Gay Men’s Chorus and co-chairing their resource development committee.  He has also had varying roles volunteering with Rainbow Families, COLAGE (Children of Lesbians and Gays Everywhere), Muscular Dystrophy Association and Juvenile Diabetes Association.\r\n','Project 515 Board','','inherit','open','open','','37-revision-3','','','2011-03-26 17:20:53','2011-03-26 22:20:53','',37,'http://fcw.lan/37-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(43,4,'2011-03-26 17:24:13','2011-03-26 22:24:13','<strong>Project 515 Donors, Making A Difference</strong>\r\n\r\nWe gratefully acknowledge our donors.  Project 515’s work is made possible through the generosity of a growing number of supporters.  We are pleased to recognize the special role these supporters play in Project 515’s success.\r\n\r\n<strong>$10,000 and Above</strong>\r\nThe F.R. Bigelow Foundation$10,000 and Above\r\nThe F.R. Bigelow Foundation\r\nThe John Larsen Foundation\r\nJohn A. and Karen Larsen\r\nJohn E. Larsen and Michael Stewart\r\nThe Minneapolis Foundation\r\nThe Kevin J. Mossier Foundation\r\nRobert Owens\r\nThe Saint Paul Foundation\r\nThe Target Foundation\r\n\r\n<strong>$5,000 to $9,999</strong>\r\nKent Allin and Thomas Knabel\r\nLee Anderson and William Fehrenbach\r\nShayna Berkowitz and Phyllis Wiener\r\nMichael D\'Amato &amp; Kerry Spolum\r\nMilo Pinkerton and Virgil Taus\r\nDavid Piper\r\n\r\n<strong>$2,500