m> – We’re building a coalition of allies throughout the state to help us spread the equality message, tell the story of discrimination and how it affects us all. Join us!  Click here if you are interested in volunteering. To learn more about Project 515\'s legislative and political advocacy, please click here.\r\n\r\n<strong>IRS Determination Letter &amp; 990ez Review</strong>\r\nIn an effort for full financial disclosure, Project 515 and Project 515 Education Campaign have made available our tax forms and other IRS documents for public reviews.','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-4','','','2011-03-26 18:25:12','2011-03-26 23:25:12','',20,'http://fcw.lan/20-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(74,4,'2011-03-26 18:29:08','2011-03-26 23:29:08','<strong>About Project 515</strong>\r\nProject 515’s mission is to ensure that same sex couples and their families have equal rights and considerations under Minnesota law.\r\n\r\n<strong>Project 515 believes:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All families should be equally valued and respected under the law.</li>\r\n	<li>All families should be treated fairly in their homes, neighborhoods, workplaces and communities.</li>\r\n	<li>For true equality and fairness under Minnesota law to become a reality, all committed couples must share similar obligations and responsibilities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title=\"Press Releases\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/go/news/\">Press Releases</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Media Inquiries </strong>\r\nIf you are a member of the media and have an inquiry or would like to media list, please call 612.396.6162 or fill out and submit the following form:\r\n\r\n[gravityform id=4 name=Media Inquiry title=false description=false ajax=true]','Media Center','','publish','closed','closed','','media-center','','','2011-03-27 04:22:15','2011-03-27 09:22:15','',0,'http://fcw.lan/?page_id=74',7,'page','',0),(75,4,'2011-03-26 18:29:05','2011-03-26 23:29:05','','Media','','inherit','open','open','','74-revision','','','2011-03-26 18:29:05','2011-03-26 23:29:05','',74,'http://fcw.lan/74-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(76,4,'2011-03-26 17:52:01','2011-03-26 22:52:01','','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','58-revision-2','','','2011-03-26 17:52:01','2011-03-26 22:52:01','',58,'http://fcw.lan/58-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(77,4,'2011-03-26 18:29:27','2011-03-26 23:29:27','','Contact Us','','inherit','open','open','','58-revision-3','','','2011-03-26 18:29:27','2011-03-26 23:29:27','',58,'http://fcw.lan/58-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(78,4,'2011-03-26 18:53:50','2011-03-26 23:53:50','Project 515 commissioned legal research conducted by Professor Anthony Winer and others at the William Mitchell College of Law to determine the extent to which Minnesota statutes treat families differently. <a title=\"Download Unequal Under the Law\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/files/Unequal_Under_the_Law.pdf\">Unequal Under the Law: 515 Ways Minnesota Laws Discriminate Against Couples and Families</a> was published in October 2007 and outlines 515 statutes that provide rights and assign responsibilities to couples based on the legal definition of marriage. As a result, these laws exclude domestic partners who aren’t married, even if they have made lifelong commitments. For gay and lesbian couples, marriage isn’t a legal option. But their families and children still suffer significantly from this unfairness.\r\n\r\nFirst and foremost, this report is about people – not politics. Neither Project 515 nor this report is advocating for the legal recognition of same-sex marriage. Instead, this list of laws and the stories of Minnesota families affected by them are meant to broaden understanding about the importance of fairness and equality under the law. They also provide encouragement to lawmakers to seek fairness in all state statutes.\r\n\r\nIn 2010, Project 515 published an update: <a href=\"../../wp-content/uploads/2011/03/Still_Unequal_Under_the_Law.pdf\">Still_Unequal_Under_the_Law</a>.','Reports','','publish','closed','open','','reports','','','2011-03-27 06:25:37','2011-03-27 11:25:37','',62,'http://fcw.lan/?page_id=78',1,'page','',0),(79,4,'2011-03-26 18:53:10','2011-03-26 23:53:10','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','78-revision','','','2011-03-26 18:53:10','2011-03-26 23:53:10','',78,'http://fcw.lan/78-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(80,4,'2011-03-26 18:54:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2011-03-26 18:54:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://fcw.lan/?page_id=80',0,'page','',0),(81,4,'2011-03-26 18:55:57','2011-03-26 23:55:57','<a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/intropage.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-260 aligncenter\" title=\"intropage\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/intropage.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"501\" height=\"340\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe personal stories of Minnesota families illustrate the very real harm that at least 515 Minnesota laws inflict. We hope these stories empower others to talk about their own values and what kind of state they want Minnesota to be. By sharing your story, you can also encourage lawmakers to seek fairness in all Minnesota laws.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Send us your story\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/share-your-story/\">Send us your story to share.</a>\r\n\r\n<em>\"We are constantly amazed at the hurdles that are placed in the way of couples who do not have the benefit of marriage. I\'m not sure we would have the perseverance and patience necessary to continually fight for the most basic rights that are automatically afforded to people with a marriage certificate.\" –</em> Janet and David Berry\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/benefitsacceptance_thumb.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-263 alignleft\" title=\"benefitsacceptance_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/benefitsacceptance_thumb.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/it%E2%80%99s-not-about-benefits-but-acceptance/\">It’s Not About Benefits, But Acceptance</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/fairness-and-respect-are-needed-especially-during-difficult-times/\"></a><a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/fairnessrespect_thumb1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-472\" title=\"KONICA MINOLTA DIGITAL CAMERA\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/fairnessrespect_thumb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/fairness-and-respect-are-needed-especially-during-difficult-times/\">Fairness and Respect Are Needed Especially During Difficult Times</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/insurancelaw_thumb.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-270 alignleft\" title=\"insurancelaw_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/insurancelaw_thumb.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/navigating-the-inequality-of-insurance-law/\">Navigating the Inequality of Insurance Law</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/fighting-to-keep-one%E2%80%99s-home/\"></a><a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/keephome_thumb1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-476\" title=\"keephome_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/keephome_thumb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/fighting-to-keep-one%E2%80%99s-home/\">Fighting to Keep One’s Home</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/lifedeath_thumb.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-272 alignleft\" title=\"life&amp;death_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/lifedeath_thumb.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/unrecognized-in-life-and-death/\">Unrecognized in life and death</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/trying-to-teach-life%E2%80%99s-lessons-to-our-children/\"></a><a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/lifeslessons_thumb1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-478\" title=\"lifeslessons_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/lifeslessons_thumb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/trying-to-teach-life%E2%80%99s-lessons-to-our-children/\">Trying to Teach Life’s Lessons to Our Children</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/missedopp_thumb1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-274 alignleft\" title=\"Two men holding hands\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/missedopp_thumb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/a-missed-opportunity-for-the-state/\">A Missed Opportunity for the State</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/a-mothers-request-for-her-babys-medical-care-information-denied/\"></a><a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/mothersrequest_thumb1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-480\" title=\"mothersrequest_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/mothersrequest_thumb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/a-mothers-request-for-her-babys-medical-care-information-denied/\">A Mother’s Request for Her Baby’s Medical Care Information: DENIED</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"Sometimes Planning and Legal Work Still Aren’t Enough\"></a><a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/planninglegal_thumb1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-486\" title=\"planninglegal_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/planninglegal_thumb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"Sometimes Planning and Legal Work Still Aren’t Enough\">Sometimes Planning and Legal Work Still Aren’t Enough</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/when-a-power-of-attorney-doesn%E2%80%99t-work-any-longer/\"></a><a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/powerattorney_thumb1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-482\" title=\"powerattorney_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/powerattorney_thumb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/when-a-power-of-attorney-doesn%E2%80%99t-work-any-longer/\">When a power of attorney doesn’t work any longer</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/tooyoung_thumb.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-278 alignleft\" title=\"tooyoung_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/tooyoung_thumb.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/unfairness-even-hurts-those-too-young-to-care-for-themselves/\">Unfairness Even Hurts Those Too Young to Care For Themselves</a>','Stories','','publish','closed','open','','stories','','','2011-03-27 06:13:27','2011-03-27 11:13:27','',62,'http://fcw.lan/?page_id=81',2,'page','',0),(82,4,'2011-03-26 18:55:40','2011-03-26 23:55:40','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','81-revision','','','2011-03-26 18:55:40','2011-03-26 23:55:40','',81,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/26/81-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(83,4,'2011-03-26 18:58:53','2011-03-26 23:58:53','Project 515 has summarized compelling economic data which demonstrated the clear case for inclusion and against consideration of any Constitutional Amendment which would seek to permanently deny recognition of gay and lesbian couples and families in Minnesota, and which would harm jobs and Minnesota\'s economy.\r\n\r\nRead this first supporting document from Project 515 that details how leading employers in Minnesota embrace inclusion, and why anti-inclusive policies like the Amendment are so clearly bad for jobs, the economy, and families:\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Download support inclusion\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/files/Support_Inclusion.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Support Inclusion, Not Anti-Jobs/Anti-Family Amendment</a>','Support Inclusion','','publish','closed','closed','','support-inclusion','','','2011-03-27 02:58:31','2011-03-27 07:58:31','',62,'http://fcw.lan/?page_id=83',3,'page','',0),(84,4,'2011-03-26 18:58:50','2011-03-26 23:58:50','','Business Talking Points','','inherit','open','open','','83-revision','','','2011-03-26 18:58:50','2011-03-26 23:58:50','',83,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/26/83-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(85,4,'2011-03-26 18:59:49','2011-03-26 23:59:49','What attaches people to their communities? What makes a community a desirable place to live? What draws people to stake their future in it? Are communities with more attached residents better off?\r\n\r\nGallup and the John S. and James L. Knight Foundation launched the Knight Soul of the Community project in 2008 with these questions in mind. After interviewing close to 43,000 people in 26 communities over three years, the study has found that inclusivity, or how welcoming a place is, is a key factor for communities with attached residents.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Read the Soul of the Community report\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/files/OVERALL.pdf\">Read the Soul of the Community report</a>','Soul of the Community','','publish','closed','closed','','soul-of-the-community','','','2011-03-27 02:59:01','2011-03-27 07:59:01','',62,'http://fcw.lan/?page_id=85',4,'page','',0),(86,4,'2011-03-26 18:59:46','2011-03-26 23:59:46','','Soul of the Community','','inherit','open','open','','85-revision','','','2011-03-26 18:59:46','2011-03-26 23:59:46','',85,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/26/85-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(87,4,'2011-03-26 19:17:41','2011-03-27 00:17:41','Project 515’s message is resonating because we’re focusing on people — Minnesotans who are our neighbors, friends, family members and coworkers. Personal stories illustrate the very real harm that at least 515 Minnesota laws inflict on our communities. By sharing your story, you will help others understand the importance of working toward fairness under Minnesota law. Personal stories will also provide encouragement to other Minnesotans, as well as lawmakers, to seek fairness in all state statutes.\r\n\r\nIf you have a personal story to share, but are uncomfortable with writing, please send us your contact information including phone number, so we can contact you to hear your personal story. Your information will be kept completely confidential unless you grant us permission to share your story with others.\r\n\r\nPlease provide us with the following:\r\n[gravityform id=2 name=ShareYour Story title=false description=false ajax=true]\r\n\r\n\r\n','Share Your Story','','publish','closed','open','','share-your-story','','','2011-03-27 01:09:51','2011-03-27 06:09:51','',81,'http://fcw.lan/?page_id=87',1,'page','',0),(88,4,'2011-03-26 19:17:34','2011-03-27 00:17:34','','Share Your Story','','inherit','open','open','','87-revision','','','2011-03-26 19:17:34','2011-03-27 00:17:34','',87,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/26/87-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(89,4,'2011-03-26 19:18:48','2011-03-27 00:18:48','','Volunteer Opportunities','','draft','closed','open','','volunteer-opportunities','','','2011-03-27 04:34:47','2011-03-27 09:34:47','',67,'http://fcw.lan/?p