 Tom’s legal next of kin to sign the release for Tom’s body and make funeral arrangements because Minnesota law didn’t recognize their relationship. The Cremation Society employee, gracious but resolute, told Randy his power of attorney ended when Tom died.\n\n“All of a sudden you’re an outsider,” Randy said. “For hours each and every day for five months, I was there as Tom’s partner. Yet I’m not allowed to take on the final responsibility and carry out Tom’s wishes. We need to turn that around.”','When a power of attorney doesn’t work any longer','','inherit','open','open','','253-autosave','','','2011-03-27 03:31:49','2011-03-27 08:31:49','',253,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/27/253-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(348,4,'2011-01-12 12:20:20','2011-01-12 18:20:20','On Wednesday, January 12, 2011 Project 515, Quorum and the Minneapolis Chamber of Commerce came together to produce a Webinar entitled <a title=\"Link to webinar\" href=\"http://mediasite.csom.umn.edu/mediasite/SilverlightPlayer/Default.aspx?peid=d9a29105f0384b1184923d41e6e6afdf\" target=\"_blank\">515 Ways Equality Makes Good Business Sense</a>. Many thanks to panelists Project 515 Executive Director Ann Kaner-Roth, Quorum Executive Director Sam McClure, VP of RBC Weath Management  Darla Kashian, Chief Executive Officer of RBC Wealth Management John Taft and to Luz Maria Hernandez for facilitating the panel.','515 Ways Equality Makes Good Business Sense','','publish','open','open','','515-ways-equality-makes-good-business-sense','','','2011-03-27 03:52:53','2011-03-27 08:52:53','',0,'http://fcw.lan/?p=348',0,'post','',0),(349,4,'2011-03-27 03:46:21','2011-03-27 08:46:21','On Wednesday, January 12, 2011 Project 515, Quorum and the Minneapolis Chamber of Commerce came together to produce a Webinar entitled 515 Ways Equality Makes Good Business Sense. Many thanks to panelists Project 515 Executive Director Ann Kaner-Roth, Quorum Executive Director Sam McClure, VP of RBC Weath Management  Darla Kashian, Chief Execu