rk Still Aren’t Enough</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/when-a-power-of-attorney-doesn%E2%80%99t-work-any-longer/\"></a><a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/powerattorney_thumb1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-482\" title=\"powerattorney_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/powerattorney_thumb1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/when-a-power-of-attorney-doesn%E2%80%99t-work-any-longer/\">When a power of attorney doesn’t work any longer</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/tooyoung_thumb.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-278 alignleft\" title=\"tooyoung_thumb\" src=\"http://fcw.lan/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/tooyoung_thumb.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Project 515\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/educate/stories/unfairness-even-hurts-those-too-young-to-care-for-themselves/\">Unfairness Even Hurts Those Too Young to Care For Themselves</a>','Stories','','inherit','open','open','','81-revision-17','','','2011-03-27 06:13:03','2011-03-27 11:13:03','',81,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/27/81-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),(491,8,'2011-03-27 05:46:09','2011-03-27 10:46:09','Project 515’s mission is to ensure that same sex couples and their families have equal rights and considerations under Minnesota law.\r\n\r\n<strong>Project 515 believes:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All families should be equally valued and respected under the law.</li>\r\n	<li>All families should be treated fairly in their homes, neighborhoods, workplaces and communities.</li>\r\n	<li>For true equality and fairness under Minnesota law to become a reality, all committed couples must share similar obligations and responsibilities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Project 515’s Beginnings</strong>\r\nMinnesotans from all walks of life came together as Project 515 following a 2006 public opinion survey sponsored by Equality Minnesota. The survey, conducted by Decision Resources, Ltd. of Minneapolis, discovered:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Nearly eight out of 10 Minnesotans said government should treat people no differently because of their sexual orientation.</li>\r\n	<li> Almost 70 percent of Minnesotans agreed that “gays and lesbians should have the same rights and responsibilities as everyone else.”</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUnfortunately, Minnesota’s laws aren’t living up to Minnesotans’ expectations. There is a significant gap between the fairness Minnesotans value and what actually occurs under Minnesota law. That’s why Project 515 commissioned legal research conducted by Professor Anthony Winer and others at William Mitchell College of Law in St. Paul. The research forms the basis for the report: Unequal Under the Law: 515 Ways Minnesota Laws Discriminate Against Couples and Families, which identifies at least 515 state laws that discriminate against families based on marriage. In 2010, Project 515 released an update to the original report, Still Unequal Under the Law.\r\n\r\n<strong>Strengthening Minnesota Families and Communities</strong>\r\nProject 515 and the report are about people.  Project 515 is dedicated to achieving full equality for committed same-sex couples in Minnesota. Research shows that 79 percent of Minnesotans believe in equality for same-sex couples, but differ on the ultimate means for providing equality. Our goal is to educate Minnesotans first about the discrimination same-sex couples face and then lead Minnesotans in a discussion about the best way to achieve full equality.\r\n\r\nProject 515 is committed to changing the debate around long-term same-sex relationships. The first step is clarifying the discrimination families currently face in Minnesota and understanding how that discrimination affects all of us.\r\nWe also recognize that in leaving out many committed couples, some state laws offer unmarried, committed couples freedom from the obligations and responsibilities placed upon married couples. Project 515 believes that fairness means all committed couples must share similar obligations and responsibilities. This will only strengthen Minnesota families and communities.\r\n\r\n<strong>Project 515 Education Campaign initiatives</strong>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Communications and Public Relations</strong></em> – Project 515 Education Campaign educates Minnesotans about the discrimination and inequality that exist for same-sex couples and their families in our state through a comprehensive Communications and Public Relations campaign. More specifically:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><em><strong>Community visits</strong></em> – Project 515 volunteers meet with political, religious, education and community leaders throughout the state to begin a dialogue on the lack of equal rights and potential solutions. The visits also include presentations to business, religious and educational organizations.</li>\r\n	<li><em><strong>Media relations</strong></em> – We reach out to reporters and editors via in-person meetings and interviews, op-ed pieces, news releases and letters to the editor.</li>\r\n	<li><em><strong>Business Leadership</strong></em> – We partner with businesses and business schools to continue to build a case for why equality makes good business and economic sense. With hundreds of Minnesota employers that provide domestic partnership benefits, it is clear that Minnesota needs to follow the lead of business and treat same-sex couples equally.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><strong>Project Partners</strong></em> – We’re building a coalition of allies throughout the state to help us spread the equality message, tell the story of discrimination and how it affects us all. Join us!  Click here if you are interested in volunteering. To learn more about Project 515\'s legislative and political advocacy, please click here.\r\n','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','20-revision-7','','','2011-03-27 05:46:09','2011-03-27 10:46:09','',20,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/27/20-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(493,6,'2011-03-27 06:12:18','2011-03-27 11:12:18','','Learn About Project 515','','inherit','open','open','','485-revision-2','','','2011-03-27 06:12:18','2011-03-27 11:12:18','',485,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/27/485-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(498,8,'2011-03-27 05:52:59','2011-03-27 10:52:59','<strong>IRS Determination Letter &amp; 990ez Review</strong>\r\nIn an effort for full financial disclosure, Project 515 and Project 515 Education Campaign have made available our tax forms and other IRS documents for public reviews.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"Link to file\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/files/Project_515_990_2008.PDF\">Project 515 990 2008</a>\r\n<a title=\"Link to file\" href=\"http://fcw.lan/files/Project_515_990_2009.PDF\"> Project 515 990 2009 </a>','Financial Statements','','inherit','open','open','','47-revision-6','','','2011-03-27 05:52:59','2011-03-27 10:52:59','',47,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/27/47-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),(494,6,'2011-03-27 06:17:16','2011-03-27 11:17:16','&lt;iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/21547860?title=0&amp;amp;byline=0&amp;amp;portrait=0\" width=\"400\" height=\"300\" frameborder=\"0\"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://vimeo.com/21547860\"&gt;Project 515 Video&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"http://vimeo.com/user6366502\"&gt;InGroupCompanies&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"http://vimeo.com\"&gt;Vimeo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;','Learn About Project 515','','inherit','open','open','','485-revision-3','','','2011-03-27 06:17:16','2011-03-27 11:17:16','',485,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/27/485-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(495,8,'2011-03-27 06:01:23','2011-03-27 11:01:23','<strong>Affiliated Organizations</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Project 515 Education Campaign</strong>\r\n\r\nProject 515 Education Campaign is committed to educating Minnesotans about the lack of equal rights for same-sex couples and their families and its impact on our state.  It is part of a family of organizations along with Project 515.\r\n\r\nWe envision a world of equality where all families are equally valued and respected under the law and in their homes, neighborhoods, workplaces, and communities.\r\n<blockquote><em>Project 515 Education Campaign initiatives </em>\r\n\r\n<em>Communications and Public Relations – </em>\r\n\r\n<em>Project 515 Education Campaign educates Minnesotans about the discrimination and inequality that exist for same-sex couples and their families in our state through a comprehensive Communications and Public Relations campaign. More specifically:</em>\r\n<em>Community visits – Project 515 volunteers meet with political, religious, education and community leaders throughout the state to begin a dialogue on the lack of equal rights and potential solutions. The visits also include presentations to business, religious and educational organizations. </em>\r\n<em>Media relations – We reach out to reporters and editors via in-person meetings and interviews, op-ed pieces, news releases and letters to the editor.</em>\r\n<em>Business Leadership – We partner with businesses and business schools to continue to build a case for why equality makes good business and economic sense. With hundreds of Minnesota employers that provide domestic partnership benefits, it is clear that Minnesota needs to follow the lead of business and treat same-sex couples equally.</em></blockquote>\r\n<strong>Project 515 Political Action Committee</strong>\r\n\r\nProject 515 Political Action Committee endorses fair-minded candidates and supports the campaigns of policy leaders who advocate for full equality for all Minnesota families.','Affiliated Organizations','','inherit','open','open','','45-revision-4','','','2011-03-27 06:01:23','2011-03-27 11:01:23','',45,'http://fcw.lan/2011/03/27/45-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(496,6,'2011-03-27 06:18:23','2011-03-27 11:18:23','&lt;iframe src=\"http://player.vi